Description: Cortex Linux core system - AI-powered package management
 This meta-package installs the core Cortex Linux system components
 required for AI-powered package management and system administration.
 .
 Cortex Linux translates natural language commands into Linux operations,
 eliminating traditional documentation complexity for server management.
 .
 Includes command-line tools:
  - cortex-upgrade: Safe system upgrade with preflight checks and rollback
  - cortex-gpu: GPU detection, driver management, Secure Boot MOK setup
  - cortex-verify: Offline integrity and signature verification
 .
 Features:
  - Natural language package management
  - Hardware-aware optimization
  - Security sandbox (Firejail/AppArmor)
  - Offline-capable operation
  - Safe upgrade orchestration with LVM/Btrfs/ZFS snapshots
 .
 This is the minimal installation. For a full installation with
 GPU support and extended tooling, install cortex-full instead.
